---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageIntro from "../components/PageIntro.astro";
import { withBase } from "../config/content";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Dustooned.">
  <div class="content-shell">
    <PageIntro
      title="About"
      eyebrow="¡Saludos!"
      description="Artist, educator, and community builder working across comics, animation, design, and interactive media."
    />
    <div class="document-actions" aria-label="Professional documents">
      <a class="button-link" href={withBase("/cv")}>CV</a>
      <a class="button-link" href={withBase("/resume")}>Resume</a>
    </div>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        I'm T'. Queer Cuban-Nicaraguan artist whose work lives at the crossroads of comics, animation, design,
        game/interactive development and education. My projects are rooted in the belief that art is not a
        privilege but a right, and a tool for empowering community by expression.
      </p>

      <h2>As a storyteller&hellip;</h2>
      <p>
        I explore themes of identity, and justice, drawing on heritage and lived experience to link personal
        memory with broader cultural struggles. Just as much, I embrace experimentation using surrealism and
        invention to disrupt expectations and push storytelling into new territory. My practice balances tradition
        with provocation, creating art that honors history while daring to imagine different futures.
      </p>

      <h2>As an educator&hellip;</h2>
      <p>
        I carry the same commitment into the classroom. Guided by my mantra "Art is Your Right" I design student
        centered programs that treat creativity as a practice of freedom. I've worked with artists of all ages and
        generations, which has taught me not only what makes learning effective, but also what inspires people to
        reclaim their own creative voice. My goal is to empower the next generation of artists to be not only
        independent creators, but also community builders who see their art as part of a larger cultural
        conversation.
      </p>

      <h2>At the heart of my work&hellip;</h2>
      <p>
        &hellip;is the belief that creativity connects us. I approach art as both cultural memory and ongoing
        experiment&mdash;honoring the histories that shape me while pushing into the surreal, the provocative, and
        the yet-to-be-imagined. Whether through teaching, storytelling, or collaboration, my goal is to create
        spaces where art is accessible, where voices are amplified, and where others feel empowered to reclaim
        their creativity.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
